**Handover doc:** `handover-edit-details-audit.md`. 6 sections, 8 open
questions surfaced for user review. Recommended scope guard: ship the
core per-league card structure + position multi-select (G1–G5, G6 if
the PR doesn't blow past ~400 LOC) in one PR; defer DOB / jersey
editability / skill-level to follow-ups.

**Load-bearing finding:**
`updatePlayerSelf` writes one position to **every active PLM** for the
player via `prisma.playerLeagueMembership.updateMany({ playerId,
toGameWeek: null })` (`actions.ts:143-146`). A user playing GK in
League A and FW in League B cannot represent that today — the form
silently overwrites both legs every time they save.

**Surfaced for user:**
- "Skill level" hint is a misread — no `skillLevel` field exists in
  schema or src. Treating as out-of-scope unless told otherwise.
- 8 design questions in §4 of the handover doc — decisions can be made
  during M2 ack or after item 1 merges.

**Next step:** M2 — wait for the multi-position-model PR (item 1) to
merge, then rebase this branch on `origin/main`, re-verify the
position shape on PLM, and lock the M3 plan against post-merge state.
**Execution does NOT start until item 1 merges.**

