**v1.82.0 surface delivered AT /account/player:**
- `PositionMultiSelect` chip-toggle component wired into the form.
- `updatePlayerSelf` accepts `positions: ReadonlyArray<string>`, validates
  per-league via `normalizePositions(raw, ballType)`, dual-writes
  `positions[]` + legacy `position` scalar.
- Page picks ONE active membership (default-league-first), passes a
  single `ballType` to the form.

**v1.82.0 did NOT fix:**
- W1 — single-league read on the page (only default league surfaces).
- W2 — `updatePlayerSelf` still writes one positions[] to ALL active
  memberships in the same transaction → multi-league players can't
  have different positions per league.
- W3 — no UI surface for paidStatus, applicationStatus, idShared,
  feeOverride, comments, jerseyNumber.
- W4 — single ballType from one league → user in soccer + futsal sees
  only one chip vocabulary.
- W5 — "set by admin" panel scalar.

**Field-location confirmation (user request):**
All five fields the user listed are **per-membership** on
`PlayerLeagueMembership`:
- `applicationStatus`, `idShared`, `paidStatus`, `feeOverride`, `comments`.
None are on `User`. → All five live on per-league cards in the new layout.

**Execution plan locked:**
- v1.83.0 (minor — new user-visible feature).
- M3: page + form scaffolding + new server actions.
- M4: read-only displays + tests.
- Phase A always; Phase B (idShared / feeOverride / comments / jersey)
  decided at end of M4 by diff size.

