## M3 — Top section + per-league card structure built

**Status:** done.

**Files written:**
- `src/app/account/player/page.tsx` — drops the `getDefaultLeagueId`
  scalar resolution; reads ALL active memberships (`toGameWeek ===
  null`) with `League.positionFees` eager-loaded for the per-card fee
  resolver. Builds `LeagueCardData[]` server-side, sorted (default-
  league first → APPROVED alphabetical → PENDING last). Empty
  `leagues` array reaches a new `<NoLeaguesNotice>` branch.
- `src/app/account/player/AccountPlayerForm.tsx` — split into
  `<ProfileSection>` (name + picture + ID-upload state, saves via
  `updatePlayerProfile`) and one `<LeagueCard>` per active membership
  (per-league save via `updatePlayerLeague`, scoped). Each card
  carries its own `useState` + Save button. Position chips use the
  card's own `ballType`. Renders application-pending badge,
  membership-status badge (when not ACTIVE), team display, jersey
  number (read-only), fee + paid badge (via `formatJpyFee`), idShared
  toggle, applicant comments quoted back read-only.
- `src/app/account/player/actions.ts` — split monolithic
  `updatePlayerSelf` into `updatePlayerProfile({ name })` (player-
  level, no PLM writes) and `updatePlayerLeague({ leagueId,
  positions?, idShared? })` (per-league). Owner gate scopes lookup
  via `findFirst({ playerId, leagueId, toGameWeek: null })` and write
  via `updateMany` scoped the same way. Validates positions per the
  membership's `ballType`. Dual-writes legacy `position` scalar only
  when `positions` is supplied. No-op (no positions, no idShared)
  skips the write entirely but still revalidates.

**Phase decision:** Phase A + Phase B fit one PR. Final form ships
with positions multi-select + idShared toggle as the editables, plus
team / app-status / membership-status / fee + paid / jersey / comments
as read-only displays.

